e asparagus into it. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Remove Varoma and set aside. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and transfer broad beans into a bowl of cold water for 2 minutes to cease cooking. Place asparagus into a large bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Peel broad beans, discard pods and add to beans in large bowl with asparagus."},{"content":"Add spring onions\/shallots, lemon zest and juice, spinach, avocado and watercress into large bowl with beans and asparagus. Season with salt and pepper and set aside."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Dressing"},{"content":"Place olive oil, grapseed oil, sugar, mustard powder, vinegar, salt and pepper into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>."},{"content":"To serve, place drained lupin flakes onto a serving platter. Place reserved vegetables on the side, then sprinkle with feta cheese and drizzle with dressing before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","You can buy lupin flakes at health food stores or online.","You can store dressing in a sealable jar in the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","45m","4 portions"]}